HEADWORD: Whitleather
<hw>Whit"leath`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>White</ets> + <ets>leather</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Leather dressed or tawed with alum, salt, etc.,
remarkable for its pliability and toughness; white leather.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The paxwax. See
<er>Paxwax</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whitling</ent>⟦br⟧
